 Graphics</A> design$ 25.00 for each <A HREF="#AudVid">Audio</A> file provided in AU/AIFF wave format$ 25.00 for each 100 kilobytes of <A HREF="#AudVid">Audio</A> provided on compact disc or tape   call to discuss <A HREF="#AudVid">Video</A> provided in MPEG format   call to discuss <A HREF="#AudVid">Video</A> provided on VHS tape</pre><p><A NAME="IS"><H2>Customer Internet Response Services</H2></A><pre>$ 75.00 for each <A HREF="#Forms">Interactive Form</A> (includes Submit Button and 3 Input Fields)$ 25.00 for each additional <A HREF="#Forms">Interactive Input Field</A>$ 60.00 for each Interactive Form List   call to discuss <A HREF="#Forms">Custom Server Software</A>$ 25.00 per month for order forwarding via <A HREF="#Forms">email</A> <I>(billed by web provider)</I>   call to discuss order forwarding via <A HREF="#Forms">fax</A> <I>(billed by web provider)</I>   call to discuss online <A HREF="#Forms">credit card</A> verification$ 50.00 to add your storefront to an existing <A HREF="#Forms">online shopping mall</A>   call to discuss creating a completely <A HREF="#Forms">new mall or catalog</A> exclusively for your products</pre><p><A NAME="CS"><H2>Internet Presence Consultation</H2></A><pre>$ 50.00 for each hour of <A HREF="#Consult">Initial Consultation</A> <i>(becomes credit on first order)</i>$ 50.00 for each hour spent helping you select a <A HREF="#Provider">Local Access Provider</A>$ 50.00 for <A HREF="#Provider">setting you up</A> with a Local Access Provider$ 50.00 for each hour spent helping you select a <A HREF="#Site">Web Server Site</A>$150.00 for each hour of <A HREF="#Consult">Custom Concept Design</A> work   call to discuss <A HREF="#Consult">Automatic Site Maintenance</A> alternatives</pre><p><A NAME="DD"><H2>Information Distribution and Storage</H2></A><pre>    n/c for the first megabyte <A HREF="#Site">uploaded to your web site</A>$ 25.00 for each additional megabyte <A HREF="#Site">uploaded to your web site</A>$ 25.00 for each megabyte <A HREF="#Site">downloaded from our site</A>$ 20.00 for each <A HREF="#Site">DOS floppy</A> mailed to you$ 25.00 for each <A HREF="#Site">MAC floppy</A> mailed to you$ 50.00 for each <A HREF="#Site">DAT tape</A> mailed to you         <i>Federal Express available in most areas at an extra charge</i>$  5.00 per month for each megabyte of <A HREF="#Site">data stored</A> at your web site <I>(billed by provider)</I>$  1.00 for each megabyte of <A HREF="#Site">data accessed</A> from your web site <I>(billed by provider)</I>$100.00 for Blast Announcing your pages to the 7 most pertinent <A HREF="#Blast">What's New Lists</A>$250.00 for Blast Announcing your pages to the 20 hottest <A HREF="#Blast">Robots, Worms, Indexes, and Lists</A><I>Effective May, 1995 -- All prices subject to change without notice</I></pre><p>Return to the <IMG SRC ="svni_icon.gif"> <aHREF="svni.html">SVNI Internet Presence Service</a> <A NAME="Package"><hr><H2>"IBIS" Instant Business by Internet Showcase</H2></a>For most people, the World Wide Web is a new and unfamiliar entity.  Because the possibilities are endless, determining and pricing exactly what you need can get confusing.  IBIS is offered to eliminate some of the confusion.<p>Our <B>Three Page Starter</B> package is designed for small budgets or those of you who are interested, yet skeptical. The package only includes items that are absolutely necessary to get a professional looking web page up. Text data must be provided to SVNI in ASCII format and limited to 300 words. The logo image must be provided in GIF format scaled to the desired size.   This <A HREF="sample.html">sample page</A> is 330 words, the logo is 85x100, and the total data size is 2850 bytes.  (Note: at this size, the web site charges would be $5.00/month for storage and $1.00 for every 368 people that accessed the page)<p>The <B>Instant Response</B> package includes everything in the Single Page Starter plus a basic form.  Interested viewers fill out the form and submit it to the web site.  Software at the web site extracts the information from the form and e-mails it to you. (Note: the web site charge for the extracting/emailing service is $25.00/month)<p><A HREF="#PKG">Back to Price Guide</A><p><A NAME="Base"><hr><H2>Base Text Pages</H2></a>Each page of a web document starts as a Base Text Page consisting of up to 50 lines of typed text. We will accept your <B>text data files</B> in any of the common word processor formats but we prefer straight ASCII.<p>Web pages layout differently than traditional printed pages.  So, unless you are familiar with the HTML display language, don't spend too much time arranging your text for output.  Formatting the text for HTML is included in the base text page pricing. In general, HTML text may include numbered lists,bullet point lists, headings, titles, sub-titles, <i>italicized</i> and <b>emphasized</b> words and phrases.<p>If you don't possess the time or equipment to provide the data to us on disk, send us your <B>typed or hand written text</B> and we will enter it into the computer for you. Also, if you already have <b>work in progress</b> but not the time or expertise to complete the job, we can finish it for you.<p>The Web does not restrict your flexibility like traditional advertising. Once your pages are installed, we can update them with <B>minor changes</B> or even completely revamp the information with <B>major changes</B> at any time. Changes required due to our error are, of course, no extra charge.<p><A HREF="#HPA">Back to Price Guide</A><A NAME="Links"><hr><H2>Page Links</H2></a>When properly linked, words and images selected by the user can reference other base pages within other web documents virtually anywhere in the world.<p><b>External Page Links</b> reference pages within <i>other</i> web documents. Although often quite desirable, you have no control over external links.  They could be changed at any time by their rightful owners. Extra validation is required when referencing external links.  And, over time, extra maintenance is required to ensure that your links continue to reference valid documents.  <b>Internal Page Links</b> reference pages within <i>your</i> web document. Internal links are easier to maintain because you own and control all the pages in question. <b>Internal Return Links</b> allow viewers to easily jump back to logical starting points within your pages.<p><i>Note: if any link within your web pages suddenly starts generating any kind of error, please contact SVNI immediately!</i><p><A HREF="#HPA">Back to Price Guide</A><A NAME="Images"><hr><H2>Your Graphics Images</H2></a>Graphics can be used to dramatically improve the look of your pages.  The standard web image display formats are <B>GIF for flat color images</B> and <B>JPEG for full color images</B>. For obvious reasons, we prefer to receive your images in either of these formats.  We can also <B>convert images from many other formats</B> including bmp, ico, iff, pcx, pict, tga, tiff, and many others.  Image files can be uploaded or mailed to our site.<p>If you don't possess the time, equipment, and/or expertise to provide us with images on disk, we can also scan data into the computer from your <B>camera ready art or photographs</B>.<p>Once the image data exists in GIF format, additional processing can be done to further enhance the images.  <B>Transparency</B> can be added to eliminate the typical block look of raster graphics files.  Data in the GIF files can also be <B>interlaced</B> for less perceived downtime during graphics display.  Rather than having long pauses during image display, interlaced files quickly get a &quotblocky&quot or &quotblurry&quot image onto the screen and then slowly refine the image before the viewer's eyes.<p><A HREF="#HPA">Back to Price Guide</A><A NAME="Art"><hr><H2>Icon and Clip Art Images</H2></a>Icons are small images that represent an action or idea.  Clip art is computer art that is created, bundled, and sold expressly for reuse. There are many sets of standard icons and clip art available on the net.  At SVNI, we have assembled our own representative sample set of <B>Stock Images</B>.  Many of these images are known to be in the public domain.  We have purchased the rights to use others.  Please note that the prices associated with these images reflect the <I>labor cost</I> of making the icons accessible from within your documents and should in no way imply that you are purchasing ownership of the original artwork.<p>If a stock image does not exist to suit your needs, we can create <B>Custom Images</B> for you.  Custom images that represent common, general purpose ideas may be added to the SVNI stock library.<p>Once we have included an icon or clip art image in your document, all other occurrences of that image within that document can be offerred to you at a lesser charge.  This applies to both stock and custom icons.  In this way, fancy bullet points and various other indicators can be used to spice up your documents at relatively little cost. The reuse of icons will also reduce your overall data storage charges since the image only needs to reside on the disk one time.<p><A HREF="#HPA">Back to Price Guide</A><A NAME="Back"><hr><H2>Custom Backgrounds and Title Graphics</H2></a>Give your pages a classy look with custom <B>Background and Title Graphics</B>.  We can take your existing logo or letterhead and use it to create some very interesting effects. <p>If you don't have or don't like your existing logo, we can create one for you.<p><A HREF="#HPA">Back to Price Guide</A><A NAME="AudVid"><hr><H2>Audio and Video</H2></a>The Web also offers Audio and Video capabilities to give your pages a multimedia look and feel.  When used appropriately, select audio and video can put a nice finishing touch on your pages.  We can work from a variety of audio and video formats, but digital is always preferred.<p><A HREF="#HPA">Back to Price Guide</A><A NAME="Forms"><hr><H2>Customer Internet Response Service</H2></a>One of the more powerful features of the Web allows users to <I>interact</I> with your web pages. The most common interaction present on the web today is the <B>Interactive Form</B>. Forms allow users to do things like fill out a questionnaire or even place an order for your product right from the screen! Each different type of interaction requires a special program to be running on the web server. When the user submits the form, each <B>interactive input field</B> is transmitted to the web server for processing.  SVNI offers <B>Custom Server Software</B> tailored to provide you with the information you need.  For example, our web software can receive submitted orders, verify the given <B>credit card</B>, then forward the order on to you either via <B>email</B> or <B>fax</B>.  Custom solutions are only limited by your imagination!<p>SVNI can also add your advertising to existing online <B>computer shopping malls</B>.  Or, if you have a whole product line or catalog of your own, we can create an brand <B>new mall or catalog</B> exclusively for you.<p><A HREF="#IS">Back to Price Guide</A><A NAME="Consult"><hr><H2>Consultation Services</H2></a>Most people are easily overwhelmed by the information that needs to be learned just to understand the Internet.  We will spend as much time as is necessary on an <B>Initial Consultation</B> to help you attain your desired level of understanding. Then, when you decide exactly what work you would like us to do, <I>the entire initial consultation fee will be credited against your first order!</I><p>The sky's the limit for possibilities on the Web. Our one on one <B>Custom Concept Design</B> can help turn your ideas into realities. We can also create an <B>Automatic Site Maintenance</B> program to monitor your pages, do regular product update changes, and make suggestions for improvements over time.<p><A HREF="#CS">Back to Price Guide</A><A NAME="Provider"><hr><H2>Local Access Providers</H2></a>If you are like most individuals and small companies, you cannot afford to maintain a dedicated &quothardwire&quot line from your computer to the Internet.  Instead, there is a much cheaper way to make your computer <I>appear</I> to be on the Internet.  Using a modem and the regular telephone lines, you can go through a <B>Local Access Provider</B> to reach the actual Internet.  The access provider's computers <I>are</I> on the Internet.  They answer your incoming call and route the connection onto the physical internet wire.<p>Access provider charges vary from as little as $10.00 to over $100.00 per month for an Internet Access Account that provides you with this connection.  There also may be an additional hourly charge. Access accounts often come with a variety of other services including email, Usenet news, ftp, gopher, wais, archie, telnet, etc...<p><B><I>It is not necessary to have an Internet Access Account to advertise on the World Wide Web.</I></B><p>Services offered, access availability, line quality, throughput speed, and price vary <I>greatly</I> between local access providers. If you think you need or want an access account, talk with us.  We can help <b>set you up</b> with a provider that offers the services you need at the best price for your area.<p><A HREF="#CS">Back to Price Guide</A><A NAME="Site"><hr><H2>Web Server Sites</H2></a>For best results, your web pages need to be accessible to the rest of the world 24 hours a day.  Web servers exist expressly for this purpose. SVNI can assist you in <B>selecting a web site</B> that best fits your needs.<p>We can <B>upload your pages</B> to any web server site you desire.  Once transferred to the web server, we wlll verify that all the pages are working properly. If you prefer to handle this yourself, you can <B>download your pages</B> from our system or we can ship your pages to you on <B>floppy disk or tape</B>.<p>In all cases, you must <I>rent</I> the disk space for your <B>data stored</B> at the web site from your web provider. Industry standard pricing is around $5.00 per megabyte per month. Also, as your pages are viewed by people around the world, the <B>data accessed</B> must be processed and transmitted by the web server. Industry standard pricing for these throughput charges is around $1.00 per megabyte.  You will typically be billed monthly <I>by your web provider</I> for these services.  (Note: most providers have a minimum monthly charge of about $25.00)<p><A HREF="#DD">Back to Price Guide</A><A NAME="Blast"><hr><H2>Blast Announcements</H2></a>Once your pages are created and placed on a web server, you must inform the world that they are there.  One straightforward way is to add your information to <b>What's New Lists</b>. Various sites around the world maintain different kinds of What's New Lists. SVNI keeps tabs of the hottest lists and can inform them of your existence. Seasoned web users peruse these lists on a regular basis.  More importantly, over time, the information added to these lists will eventually propagate itself to other lists and the robots.  While this entire process can take several months, you will likely start seeing some activity on your pages within a week.<p>This time lag can be completely eliminated by blasting your announcment directly to the hottest <b>Robots, Worms, Indexes, and Lists</b> in the world today.  SVNI knows where to place your information so that within minutes the most popular and powerful searching tools all know about you.  In all test cases, new pages were being accessed within one hour!<p><A HREF="#DD">Back to Price Guide</A><p><hr><IMG SRC ="svni_icon.gif"> <a HREF="svni.html">SVNI Internet Presence Provider</a> SVNI Fax (408) 746-2765 <a HREF="mailto:order@siliconvalley.com">order@siliconvalley.com</a><p><i>May 26, 1995</i></BODY></HTML> Service.nt <A HREF="#Blast">What's New Lists</A>$250.00 for Blast Announcing your pages to the 20 hottest <A HREF="#Blast">Robots, Worms, Indexes, and Lists</A><I>Effective May, 1995 -- All prices subject to change without notice</I></pre><p>Return to the <IMG SRC ="svni_icon.gif"> <aHREF="svni.html">SVNI Internet Presence Service</a> <A NAME="Package"><hr><H2>"IBIS" Inst␀␀␀␀␀F␀␀F␀␀F␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀J␀␀Q␀␀¨␀␀Ý␀␀Þ␀␀ß␀␀æ␀␀"␀␀(␀␀)␀␀~␀␀ß␀␀=␀␀␀␀í␀␀&␀␀_␀␀␀␀ï␀␀?␀␀¦␀␀þ␀␀T␀␀«␀␀␀␀a␀␀³␀␀	␀␀	Y␀␀	␀␀	␀␀	␀␀	¦␀␀	ç␀␀	í␀␀
