<title>DNR Home Page</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="images/whttxtr1.jpg" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p><img src="images/logo.gif" width="192" height="42"><br>
<a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/Parks/index.htm"><img
src="images/parksbar.gif" border="0" width="200" height="50"></a><a
href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/CRD/index.htm"><img
src="images/crdbar.gif" border="0" width="200" height="50"></a><a
href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/HPD/index.htm"><img
src="images/hpdbar.gif" border="0" width="200" height="50"></a><br>
<a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/EPD/index.htm"><img
src="images/epdbar.gif" border="0" width="200" height="50"></a><a
href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/WRD/index.htm"><img
src="images/wrdbar.gif" border="0" width="200" height="50"></a><a
href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/P2AD/index.htm"><img
src="images/p2adbar.gif" border="0" width="200" height="50"></a><br>
</p>
<hr>
<p>[ <a href="index.htm">Home</a> | <a href="news.htm">What's New</a>
| <a href="toc.htm">TOC</a> | <a href="feedback.htm">Feedback</a>
| <a href="search.htm">Search</a> ]</p>
<h2><a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/Parks/index.htm"><img
src="images/parks.gif" align="left" border="0" hspace="0"
width="100" height="100"></a>Parks, Recreation &amp; Historic
Sites Division</h2>
<p>&#160; Georgia&#146;s 62 State Parks and Historic Sites have
some of the southeast&#146;s most enjoyable attractions and
reasonably priced accommodations, including contemporary lodges,
rustic cottages, and shady campgrounds. <br>
&#160; </p>
<h2><a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/CRD/index.htm"><img
src="images/crd.gif" align="left" border="0" hspace="0"
width="100" height="100"></a>Coastal Resources Division</h2>
<p>The Coastal Resources Division administers programs to ensure
the wise management of Georgia's marshlands, barrier islands, and
commercial and sport marine species. Based in Brunswick, the
Division's jurisdiction includes the six coastal counties,
Chatham, Bryan, Liberty, McIntosh, Glynn, and Camden and the
coastal waters from the upper reached of tidal creeks to three
miles offshore.</p>
<h2><a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/HPD/index.htm"><img
src="images/hpd.gif" align="left" border="0" hspace="0"
width="100" height="100"></a>Historic Preservation Division</h2>
<p>As the state historic preservation office, HPD administers 13
programs authorized by federal and state laws that foster
stewardship, encourage neighborhood revitalization and support
community and economic development through the preservation and
use of historic and archaeological resources.&#160;</p>
<h2><a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/EPD/index.htm"><img
src="images/epd.gif" align="left" border="0" hspace="0"
width="100" height="100"></a>Environmental Protection Division</h2>
<p>&#160;The Environmental Protection Division (EPD) protects
Georgia's air, land, and water through the authority of state
statutes and major parts of five federal environmental statutes.
These laws regulate public and private facilities having to do
with water quality, air quality, hazardous waste, water supply,
solid waste management, surface mining, and other areas. &#160;</p>
<h2><a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/WRD/index.htm"><img
src="images/wrd.gif" align="left" border="0" hspace="0"
width="100" height="100"></a>Wildlife Resources Division</h2>
<p>&#160; Information on wildlife conservation, fishing and
hunting opportunities, wildlife law enforcement, boating,
watchable wildlife activities, endangered species, and other
wildlife-related topics.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<h2><a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/P2AD/index.htm"><img
src="images/p2ad.gif" alt="P2AD Logo" align="left" border="0"
hspace="0" width="100" height="100"></a>Pollution Prevention
Assistance Division</h2>
<p>The Pollution Prevention Assistance Division (P2AD) is a
non-regulatory, state agency that offers technical assistance to
business, industry, agriculture, government, and the general
public to reduce waste and pollution at the source or point of
production. This service is included at no cost to the clients. </p>
<p>&#160; </p>
<hr>
<h2>Contact Information</h2>
<dl>
    <dt><strong>Telephone</strong> </dt>
    <dd>See each Division for contact information.</dd>
    <dt><strong>FAX</strong> </dt>
    <dd>See each Division for contact information.</dd>
    <dt><strong>Postal address</strong> </dt>
    <dd>205 Butler Street S.E.</dd>
    <dd>Atlanta, Georgia 30334<br>
    </dd>
</dl>
