<html>
<head>
<title>Notice of Proposed Amendments to the GA Rules for Haz.
Waste Management</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/images/whttxtr1.jpg"
bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<h3 align="center"><strong>NOTICE OF PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO THE</strong> </h3>
<h3 align="center"><strong>GEORGIA RULES FOR HAZARDOUS WASTE
MANAGEMENT</strong> <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</h3>
<p>TO ALL INTERESTED PERSONS: <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>
<p>Notice is hereby given that, pursuant to the authority
contained in the Official Code of Georgia Title 12 (Conservation
and Natural Resources) Chapter 8 (Waste Management), and Article
3 (Hazardous Waste), it is proposed that the Department of
Natural Resources' rules and regulations governing the operation
of the Department be amended. Specifically, amendments to chapter
391-3-11 of the Rules of the Department of Natural Resources,
Environmental Protection Division, Hazardous Waste Management are
proposed. <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>
<p>This notice, together with an exact copy of the proposed rules
and a synopsis of the proposed rules, will be mailed to all
persons who have requested, in writing, that they be placed on a
mailing list. In addition, an exact copy of the proposed amended
rules and a synopsis of the proposed rules may be obtained from
the Information Specialist, Hazardous Waste Management Branch,
205 Butler Street, S.E., Suite 1252, Floyd Towers East, Atlanta,
GA 39334, telephone number (404) 656-7802, and at the following
Environmental Protection Region Offices: <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>
<p>Middle Georgia Regional Office S. E. Regional Office S.W.
Regional </p>
<p>EPD EPD EPD </p>
<p>2640 Shurling Drive 1 Conservation Way 2024 Newton Road </p>
<p>Macon, GA 31211 Brunswick, GA 31523-8602 Albany, GA 31708 <br
wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>
<p>To provide the public an opportunity to comment upon and
provide input into these rules, a public hearing will be held at
10:00 a.m. on November 12, 1996 in the Board Room of the
Department of Natural Resources, Suite 1252 Floyd Towers East,
205 Butler Street, Atlanta, GA. Any participant at the public
hearing may submit data, make a statement, comment, or offer
views or arguments, either orally or in writing. Statements
should be concise to permit everyone an opportunity to be heard.
Participants in the hearing are requested to register on arrival
and to notify the registering official of their intent to give a
statement. <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>
<p>For those unable to attend the hearing, written statements may
be submitted for consideration prior to the close of business on
November 13, 1996. Statements should be mailed to: <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>
<p align="center">Jennifer Kaduck, Chief </p>
<p align="center">Hazardous Waste Management Branch </p>
<p align="center">Environmental Protection Division </p>
<p align="center">205 Butler Street, N.E. </p>
<p align="center">Suite 1154, Floyd Towers East </p>
<p align="center">Atlanta, Georgia 30334 <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>
<p>The Board of Natural Resources will consider the adoption of
these proposed rules during its regular meeting on December 4,
1996, which begins at 9:00 a.m. in the Board Room of the
Department of Natural Resources located at Suite 1252, Floyd
Towers East, 205 Butler Street, S.E., Atlanta, GA 30334. </p>
</body>
</html>
