<html>
<head>
<title>Hazardous Waste Branch Narrative</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body background="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/images/whttxtr1.jpg"
bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<h1 align="center"><b>HAZARDOUS WASTE MANAGEMENT BRANCH</b> </h1>
<h3 align="center"><b>Jennifer R. Kaduck, Chief</b> <br>
<b>205 Butler Street, S.E.</b> <br>
<b>Floyd Towers East, Suite 1154</b> <br>
<b>Atlanta, Georgia 30334</b> <br>
<b>404/656-7802</b> </h3>
<hr>
<p>The Hazardous Waste Management Branch has the responsibility
of administering the programs associated with the Georgia
Hazardous Waste Management Act, Hazardous Site Response Act and
their Federal analogues under RCRA and CERCLA. </p>
<h3><b>CORRECTIVE ACTION PROGRAM</b> </h3>
<p><b>Bill Mundy, Program Manager</b> <br>
<b>404/656-7802</b> </p>
<p>Suite 1154, Floyd Towers East </p>
<p>404/656-7802 Fax 404/651-9425 </p>
<p>The Corrective Action Program serves the Hazardous Waste
Management Branch in two primary ways. The Land Disposal and
Remedial Sites Units perform inspections, permitting,
enforcement, CERCLA activities, and all types of corrective
action for releases from treatment, storage, or disposal
facilities and other facilities that have releases into the
environment. The Hazardous Waste Support Unit provides other
services to the entire branch including, but not limited to: data
management, public information, program authorization and
rulemaking. The Risk Assessment Unit serves the entire Branch by
providing risk assessments and related information. </p>
<h3><b>FACILITIES COMPLIANCE PROGRAM</b> </h3>
<p><b>Jim Ussery, Program Manager</b> <br>
<b>404/656-2833</b> </p>
<p>Suite 1162, Floyd Towers East </p>
<p>404/656-2833 Fax 404/651-9425 </p>
<p>The Facilities Compliance Program handles hazardous waste
permitting and compliance (inspection and enforcement) for
government facilities, commercial hazardous waste facilities and
hazardous waste combustion facilities which treat, store or
dispose of hazardous waste on site. </p>
<h3><b>GENERATOR COMPLIANCE PROGRAM</b> </h3>
<p><b>Ren&eacute;e Hudson Goodley, Program Manager</b> <br>
<b>404/657-8831</b> </p>
<p>Suite 1066, Floyd Towers East </p>
<p>404/657-8831 Fax 404/657-7379 </p>
<p>The Generator Compliance Program has overall responsibility
for compliance and enforcement activities at hazardous waste
facilities not requiring hazardous waste permits (facilities that
do not treat, store or dispose of hazardous waste at their
facilities). This program consists of two units. The types of
hazardous waste facilities handled by this Program include:
large, small and conditionally exempt small quantity generators,
transporters and used oil/fuel generators, marketers and burners.
The program also provides technical assistance for the commercial
reclamation of batteries and antifreeze. </p>
<h3><b>HAZARDOUS SITES RESPONSE PROGRAM</b> </h3>
<p><b>Tim Cash, Program Manager</b> <br>
<b>404/657-8600</b> </p>
<p>Suite 1462, Floyd Towers East </p>
<p>404/ 657-8600 Fax 404/657-0807 </p>
<p>The Hazardous Sites Response Program is responsible for
requiring corrective action at sites where there have been
releases of hazardous wastes, hazardous substances and hazardous
constituents. Fees that are collected on hazardous and solid
wastes managed in Georgia are deposited into the Hazardous Waste
Trust Fund which may then be used to clean-up sites where
responsible parties are unwilling or unable to clean-up the site
themselves. A Hazardous Sites Inventory (HSI) is published each
year. The Program also oversees HSI sites being investigated and
cleaned up by private parties. </p>
<hr>
<p>8/96 </p>
</body>
