<title>Proposed Rules</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body background="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/images/whttxtr1.jpg"
bgcolor="#FFFFFF" stylesrc="index.htm">

<h1>Proposed Rules</h1>

<p>[ <a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/index.htm">Home</a> | <a
href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/news.htm">What's New</a> | <a
href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/toc.htm">TOC</a> | <a
href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/feedback.htm">Feedback</a> | <a
href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/search.htm">Search</a> ]</p>

<p align="left"><strong>NEW!</strong>(11/25/96) <a
href="pcb/not_1296.html">Notice of Postponed Date for Board
Consideration of Proposed</a><br>
<a href="pcb/not_1296.html">Revisions to Georgia Rules for
Radioactive Materials</a></p>

<p align="left"><br>
<strong>NEW!</strong> <a
href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/HWB/pubnot.htm">Notice of
Proposed Amendments to the Georgia Rules for Hazardous Waste
Mangement</a><br>
<a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/HWB/synopsis.htm">Read a
syopsis of the proposed Amendments</a><br>
<a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/HWB/summnew.htm">Read a
summary of the proposed changes to the Rules</a><br>
<a href="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/HWB/rulesdrf.htm">Download
the draft Rules Chapter 391-3-11</a></p>

<p>The Environmental Protection Division (EPD) of the Georgia
Department of Natural Resources has previously announded a
comment period on proposed additions to Georgia's Water Quality
Control Rules, Chapter 391-3-6-.07 (Surface Water Withdrawals),
and Ground Water Use Rules, Chapter 391-3-2. The proposed
amendments would include revisions to the duration surface and
ground water withdrawal permits for non-farm water withdrawal
applications.</p>

<p>It was announced on August 29, 1996 that the proposed Rules
amendments would be considered for adoption by the Board of
Natural Resources on October 23, 1996. Today's notice is to
announce that the proposed amendments will not be considered at
the October 23rd meeting. EPD will follow up with another public
notice as soon as it is determined when the porposed amendments
will be places on the board's agenda. For further imformation,
please contact EPD by calling Napoleon Caldwell, Manager, Water
Resources Management Program, at 404/656/3094.</p>
</body>
</html>
