content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
<title>GEORGIA EPD HOLDS SAVANNAH RIVER BASIN MANAGEMENT PLANNING
STAKEHOLDERS MEETINGS</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body stylesrc="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/EPD/index.htm">
<p>&#160;Tiffany Klebe - 404-656-4713</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><b><u>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE:</u></b></p>
<p>&#160;&#160;</p>
<p align="center"><b>GEORGIA EPD HOLDS SAVANNAH RIVER BASIN</b></p>
<p align="center"><b>MANAGEMENT PLANNING STAKEHOLDERS MEETINGS</b></p>
<p>&#160;&#160;</p>
<p>January 7, 1997 - The Environmental Protection Division (EPD)
of the Georgia Department of Natural Resources will be holding
public stakeholder meetings (sites listed below) in Hartwell,
Georgia on January 9, 1997, in Savannah, Georgia on January 13,
1997, and in Evans, Georgia on January 16, 1997, for citizens
interested in the development of the Savannah River Basin
Management Plan. The meetings will use an <font
face="WP TypographicSymbols">A</font>open house<font
face="WP TypographicSymbols">@</font> approach, and citizen input
is needed to insure the public&#146;s interests are considered in
the initial planning stages. An overview of the river basin
management planning approach for the Savannah River will be
provided. EPD associates will be available to record and discuss
issues of interest and/or concern.</p>
<p>The Georgia EPD has adopted a river basin management planning
approach to focus on an entire watershed or basin, instead of a
statewide approach as used in the past. A river basin plan will
address water quality and water use. The mission of the Georgia
River Basin Management Planning program is to develop and
implement a river basin planning program to protect, enhance, and
restore the waters of the state of Georgia that will provide for
the effective monitoring, allocation, use, regulation, and
management of water resources.</p>
<p>The stakeholder meetings will be held at the following
locations:</p>
<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p>January 9, 1997</p>
        <p>6:30 p.m. - 8:30 p.m.</p>
        <p>Hart County Library</p>
        <p>150 Benson Street</p>
        <p>Hartwell, Georgia</p>
        <p>(706) 376-4655</p>
        <p>&#160;&#160;</p>
        <p>January 13, 1997</p>
        <p>6:30 p.m. - 8:30 p.m.</p>
        <p>City Hall, 2nd Floor Council Chambers</p>
        <p>2 East Bay Street</p>
        <p>Savannah, Georgia</p>
        <p>(912) 651-6444</p>
        <p>&#160;</p>
        <p>&#160;</p>
        <p>January 16, 1997</p>
        <p>6:30 p.m. - 8:30 p.m.</p>
        <p>Evans Government Complex</p>
        <p>630 Washington West Drive</p>
        <p>Evans, Georgia</p>
        <p>(706) 868-3379</p>
        <p>&#160;</p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>
<p>If you have questions or need additional information on the
stakeholder meetings, please contact Kevin Farrell or Mork Winn
at 404-656-4905.</p>
</body>
</html>
