<body stylesrc="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/EPD/index.htm">
<p align="left">Tiffany Klebe - 404-656-4713</p>
<p>&#160;<b><u>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE:</u></b></p>
<p>&#160;&#160;</p>
<p align="center"><b>GEORGIA EPD HOLDS OGEECHEE RIVER BASIN</b></p>
<p align="center"><b>MANAGEMENT PLANNING STAKEHOLDER MEETING</b></p>
<p>&#160;&#160;</p>
<p>January 7, 1997 - The Environmental Protection Division (EPD)
of the Georgia Department of Natural Resources will be holding a
public stakeholder meeting (site listed below) in Statesboro,
Georgia on January 14, 1997, for citizens interested in the
development of the Ogeechee River Basin Management Plan. The
meetings will use an <font face="WP TypographicSymbols">A</font>open
house<font face="WP TypographicSymbols">@</font> approach, and
citizen input is needed to insure the public&#146;s interests are
considered in the initial planning stages. An overview of the
river basin management planning approach for the Ogeechee River
will be provided. EPD associates will be available to record and
discuss issues of interest and/or concern.</p>
<p>The Georgia EPD has adopted a river basin management planning
approach to focus on an entire watershed or basin, instead of a
statewide approach as used in the past. A river basin plan will
address water quality and water use. The mission of the Georgia
River Basin Management Planning program is to develop and
implement a river basin planning program to protect, enhance, and
restore the waters of the state of Georgia that will provide for
the effective monitoring, allocation, use, regulation, and
management of water resources.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>The stakeholder meeting will be held at the following
location:</p>
<blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        <p>January 14, 1997</p>
        <p>6:30 p.m. - 8:30 p.m.</p>
        <p>Statesboro City Hall</p>
        <p>50 East Main Street</p>
        <p>(912) 764-5468</p>
        <p>&#160;</p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>
<p>If you have questions or need additional information on the
stakeholder meeting, please contact Kevin Farrell or Mork Winn at
404-656-4905.</p>
